trans-unit.id: Privacy Policy Updated: September 25, 2023 Welcome to the GFK Digital Asset Trading Platform (referred to as "GFK" or "we"). We highly value your privacy and are committed to protecting your personal information. To ensure that you fully understand our policies and practices regarding the collection, use, and protection of your information, please read this Privacy Policy carefully. I. Introduction 1.1 This policy is designed to inform you about how we collect, use, store, and protect your personal information. We adhere to the relevant laws and regulations of Lithuania and work diligently to safeguard your privacy. 1.2 "GFK" is the English name for the GFK Digital Asset Trading Platform. In this policy, "GFK" or "we" refers to our platform. "You" refers to the users of our services. II. Types of Information Collected 2.1 We may collect the following types of information: (a) Personal Identification Information: Such as your name, identification number, email address, contact address, and phone number. (b) Financial Information: Such as your bank account number, transaction records, digital asset addresses, and more. (c) Technical Information: We may automatically collect technical information about your visits to our website or use of our applications, including IP addresses, device information, browser type, access dates, and times, among others. (d) User-Generated Content: This includes transaction information, comments, questions, and other content you provide on our platform. (e) Other Information: We may collect other types of information as required by applicable laws or with your consent. 2.2 You have the right to choose whether to provide certain types of information, but this may affect your ability to use some of our services. III. Use of Information 3.1 We may use your information for the following purposes: (a) Service Provision: This includes processing transactions, verifying identities, providing customer support, and managing your account. (b) Regulatory Requirements: Complying with applicable laws and court orders, preventing fraud, and money laundering. (c) Service Improvement: Analyzing user needs and behaviors to enhance our products and services. (d) Marketing: Sending promotional and marketing information to you with your consent. (e) Security Protection: Protecting your and our security, including preventing unauthorized access and data breaches. 3.2 We only share your information as permitted by law, such as with our partners, regulatory agencies, and law enforcement authorities. We take appropriate measures to ensure the protection of your information. IV. Information Storage and Security 4.1 Information Storage: We store your information on secure servers and employ necessary technical and organizational measures to protect it from unauthorized access, loss, damage, or disclosure. We regularly review and update security measures to address evolving threats. 4.2 Account Access Control: Access to your account requires personal password verification. Please safeguard your account information and do not share your password or authorize others to use your account. If you suspect a security breach or password compromise, please notify us immediately so we can take necessary steps to protect your account. V. Privacy Rights Protection 5.1 Information Access and Correction: You have the right to inquire about, access, and correct your personal information at any time. If you need to access or correct your information, please log in to your account or contact our customer support team, and we will promptly respond to your request. 5.2 Withdrawal of Consent: If you have previously consented to our processing of your information but later decide to withdraw your consent, please contact us. Please note that withdrawing consent may affect your ability to use our services, but it will not impact the processing of information you have already provided. 5.3 Information Deletion: In certain cases, in accordance with applicable laws and regulations, you may request the deletion of your personal information. We will fulfill your request within the bounds of the law. 5.4 Privacy Officer: If you have any questions, concerns, or complaints about this policy or your privacy rights, or if you need to exercise the rights mentioned above, please contact our Privacy Officer. We are committed to assisting you with these matters. We appreciate your attention to our Privacy Policy and your understanding. By continuing to use GFK services, you agree to the terms and conditions of this policy. If you have any further questions or need additional assistance, please feel free to contact our customer support team. VI. Policy Updates 6.1 We may periodically update this policy to reflect changes in the law and improvements to our services. Any significant changes will be posted on our website. Thank you for reading our Privacy Policy. We value your privacy and are committed to maintaining and protecting your privacy rights. If you have any other questions or need further assistance, please don't hesitate to contact our customer support team.
trans-unit.source:
Privacy Policy Updated: September 25, 2023
Welcome to the GFK Digital Asset Trading Platform (referred to as "GFK" or "we"). We highly value your privacy and are committed to protecting your personal information. To ensure that you fully understand our policies and practices regarding the collection, use, and protection of your information, please read this Privacy Policy carefully.
I. Introduction
1.1 This policy is designed to inform you about how we collect, use, store, and protect your personal information. We adhere to the relevant laws and regulations of Lithuania and work diligently to safeguard your privacy.
1.2 "GFK" is the English name for the GFK Digital Asset Trading Platform. In this policy, "GFK" or "we" refers to our platform. "You" refers to the users of our services.
II. Types of Information Collected
2.1 We may collect the following types of information:
(a) Personal Identification Information: Such as your name, identification number, email address, contact address, and phone number.
(b) Financial Information: Such as your bank account number, transaction records, digital asset addresses, and more.
(c) Technical Information: We may automatically collect technical information about your visits to our website or use of our applications, including IP addresses, device information, browser type, access dates, and times, among others.
(d) User-Generated Content: This includes transaction information, comments, questions, and other content you provide on our platform.
(e) Other Information: We may collect other types of information as required by applicable laws or with your consent. 2.2 You have the right to choose whether to provide certain types of information, but this may affect your ability to use some of our services.
III. Use of Information
3.1 We may use your information for the following purposes:
(a) Service Provision: This includes processing transactions, verifying identities, providing customer support, and managing your account.
(b) Regulatory Requirements: Complying with applicable laws and court orders, preventing fraud, and money laundering.
(c) Service Improvement: Analyzing user needs and behaviors to enhance our products and services.
(d) Marketing: Sending promotional and marketing information to you with your consent.
(e) Security Protection: Protecting your and our security, including preventing unauthorized access and data breaches.
3.2 We only share your information as permitted by law, such as with our partners, regulatory agencies, and law enforcement authorities. We take appropriate measures to ensure the protection of your information.
IV. Information Storage and Security
4.1 Information Storage: We store your information on secure servers and employ necessary technical and organizational measures to protect it from unauthorized access, loss, damage, or disclosure. We regularly review and update security measures to address evolving threats.
4.2 Account Access Control: Access to your account requires personal password verification. Please safeguard your account information and do not share your password or authorize others to use your account. If you suspect a security breach or password compromise, please notify us immediately so we can take necessary steps to protect your account.
V. Privacy Rights Protection
5.1 Information Access and Correction: You have the right to inquire about, access, and correct your personal information at any time. If you need to access or correct your information, please log in to your account or contact our customer support team, and we will promptly respond to your request.
5.2 Withdrawal of Consent: If you have previously consented to our processing of your information but later decide to withdraw your consent, please contact us. Please note that withdrawing consent may affect your ability to use our services, but it will not impact the processing of information you have already provided.
5.3 Information Deletion: In certain cases, in accordance with applicable laws and regulations, you may request the deletion of your personal information. We will fulfill your request within the bounds of the law.
5.4 Privacy Officer: If you have any questions, concerns, or complaints about this policy or your privacy rights, or if you need to exercise the rights mentioned above, please contact our Privacy Officer. We are committed to assisting you with these matters.
We appreciate your attention to our Privacy Policy and your understanding. By continuing to use GFK services, you agree to the terms and conditions of this policy. If you have any further questions or need additional assistance, please feel free to contact our customer support team.
VI. Policy Updates
6.1 We may periodically update this policy to reflect changes in the law and improvements to our services. Any significant changes will be posted on our website.
Thank you for reading our Privacy Policy. We value your privacy and are committed to maintaining and protecting your privacy rights. If you have any other questions or need further assistance, please don't hesitate to contact our customer support team.

一、简介
1.1 本政策旨在告知您我们如何收集、使用、存储和保护您的个人信息。 我们遵守立陶宛的相关法律法规，并努力保护您的隐私。

二. 收集的信息类型
2.1 我们可能收集以下类型的信息：
(a) 个人身份信息：例如您的姓名、身份证号码、电子邮件地址、联系地址和电话号码。
(b) 财务信息：例如您的银行账号、交易记录、数字资产地址等。

(e) 其他信息：我们可能会根据适用法律的要求或在您同意的情况下收集其他类型的信息。 2.2 您有权选择是否提供某些类型的信息，但这可能会影响您使用我们的某些服务的能力。
三． 信息的使用
3.1 我们可能将您的信息用于以下目的：
(a) 服务提供：这包括处理交易、验证身份、提供客户支持和管理您的帐户。
(b) 监管要求：遵守适用法律和法院命令，防止欺诈和洗钱。
(c) 服务改进：分析用户需求和行为以增强我们的产品和服务。
(d) 营销：在您同意的情况下向您发送促销和营销信息。
(e) 安全保护：保护您和我们的安全，包括防止未经授权的访问和数据泄露。
3.2 我们仅在法律允许的情况下共享您的信息，例如与我们的合作伙伴、监管机构和执法机构。 我们采取适当的措施来确保您的信息得到保护。
四． 信息存储与安全
4.1 信息存储：我们将您的信息存储在安全服务器上，并采取必要的技术和组织措施来保护其免遭未经授权的访问、丢失、损坏或披露。 我们定期审查和更新安全措施，以应对不断变化的威胁。
4.2 账户访问控制：访问您的账户需要进行个人密码验证。 请您妥善保管您的账户信息，不要泄露您的密码或授权他人使用您的账户。 如果您怀疑存在安全漏洞或密码泄露，请立即通知我们，以便我们采取必要措施来保护您的帐户。
五、隐私权保护
5.1信息查阅和更正：您有权随时查询、查阅、更正您的个人信息。 如果您需要访问或更正您的信息，请登录您的帐户或联系我们的客户支持团队，我们将及时回复您的请求。
5.2 撤回同意：如果您之前同意我们处理您的信息，但后来决定撤回您的同意，请与我们联系。 请注意，撤回同意可能会影响您使用我们服务的能力，但不会影响对您已提供的信息的处理。
5.3信息删除：在某些情况下，根据适用的法律法规，您可以要求删除您的个人信息。 我们将在法律允许的范围内满足您的要求。
5.4 隐私官：如果您对本政策或您的隐私权有任何疑问、疑虑或投诉，或者您需要行使上述权利，请联系我们的隐私官。 我们致力于协助您解决这些问题。

1.1 您使用GFK的服务即表示您接受并同意遵守本协议的所有条款和条件。 如果您不同意本协议的任何部分，请停止使用GFK的服务。
二. 平台的使用
2.1 您同意遵守立陶宛的国家政策和GFK平台的所有内部规则和规定。
2.2 您必须达到当地法律规定的法定年龄，才有权交易和使用我们的服务。
三． 账户注册
3.1 您需要注册GFK账户才能使用我们的服务。 在注册过程中，您必须提供准确的个人信息。
3.2 您有责任保护您的账户信息和密码，不应与他人分享。 如果您怀疑您的帐户安全受到损害，您应立即通知我们。
四． 服务的使用
4.1 您同意仅使用合法手段和合法资金进行交易。 您不得从事任何非法、欺诈或洗钱活动。
4.2 如果我们怀疑您违反本协议或任何相关法律法规，我们保留自行决定暂停或终止您的帐户的权利。
五、风险免责声明
5.1 您了解加密货币市场波动性很大，其价值可能会快速增加或减少。 GFK 不对您的交易损失负责。
六． 隐私政策
6.1 我们尊重您的隐私权。 请参阅我们的隐私政策，了解我们如何收集、使用和保护您的个人信息。
七． 免责声明
7.1 GFK不对因以下原因造成的任何损失承担责任：技术故障、网络连接问题、政府行为、市场波动、交易中断、黑客攻击或其他不可抗力事件。
八． 协议变更
8.1 我们保留随时更改本协议内容的权利，任何重大变更我们将通过我们的网站公告。
九． 联系我们
如果您对此协议有任何疑问或需要帮助，请联系我们的客户支持团队。
以上是GFK数字资产交易平台的用户协议。 我们希望您在使用我们的服务之前仔细阅读并理解这些条款和条件。
